Privacy Policy for kidsplaylearninggames.com Apps / Games
Effective Date:
30/01/2022
Introduction
Welcome to kidsplaylearninggames.com! We are committed to protecting the privacy and safety of our young users. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information across all apps distributed by kidsplaylearninggames.com.
Information We Collect
While we do not collect personal information such as names, email addresses, or contact numbers, we use third-party services to help us improve our apps. These services collect the following types of data:
Firebase Analytics:
We use Firebase Analytics to collect aggregated data on app usage. This data helps us understand user behavior, improve app performance, and enhance user experience. The information collected includes:
App Usage:
Information about how often and for how long the app is used, features accessed, and general usage patterns.
Device Information:
Non-personal data such as device type, operating system version, and app version.
Firebase Crashlytics:
We use Firebase Crashlytics to monitor and report app crashes and other issues. This helps us identify and fix problems to ensure a smoother experience. The information collected includes:
Crash Reports:
Data related to crashes, such as device model, operating system version, and stack traces.
In-App Purchases
Our apps may offer in-app purchases. All purchase options are protected by parental controls available within the apps to ensure that only parents can make purchases.
Advertising
Our apps may include advertisements. These ads are displayed in a manner that is appropriate for children and do not collect personal information. We encourage parents to review and manage any ad-related settings available in the apps.
Third-Party Links
Our apps may contain links to other apps or websites. These links are carefully selected to be suitable for children. However, we are not responsible for the content or privacy practices of third-party sites or apps.
Social Media
Our apps do not integrate with social media platforms such as Twitter, Facebook, or other online services.
Location Data
We do not collect or use precise geographic location information.
Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted here, and the updated policy will become effective immediately upon posting. We encourage parents to review this policy periodically to stay informed about our practices.
Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at
support@kidsplaylearninggames.com
or
dev.kidsplaylearninggames@gmail.com
.
Consent
By using our apps, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy and consent to our practices as described herein.